      "message": "READ ME SECOND\n\nhttps://www.joeshaw.org/dont-defer-close-on-writable-files/\n\nthe advice there indicates that, since you are using named return values, that you would want to do\nerr \u003d skerr.Fmt(...)\nreturn\n\nThat doc also indicates that it\u0027s generally safe, especially for files, to call .Close() multiple times.\n\nThat would simplify the readability and cover our butts if things fail elsewise.\n\nI could imagine a helper\nfunc CloseAndIgnoreError(io.Closer) {}\nthat we could do to make errcheck happy and make it clear that we are ignoring the error in the defer case.",
